        },
        "body": "Fixes an issue where the Leaderboard header controls (Search / Clear / Role filter) were not responsive on mobile viewports, causing overflow and poor usability.\r\n**What changed**\r\nUpdated components/Leaderboard/LeaderboardView.tsx header layout to stack on small screens (flex-col) and keep the current horizontal layout on sm+.\r\nMade Search and action buttons mobile-friendly by using full-width controls on small screens (w-full, sm:w-auto).\r\nConstrained the Role popover width to the viewport (max-w-[calc(100vw-2rem)]) to prevent off-screen rendering.\r\n**How to test**\r\nRun npm run dev\r\nOpen /leaderboard/month\r\nSwitch to a mobile viewport (e.g. 390×844 and 320×568)\r\n**Verify:**\r\nNo horizontal scrolling\r\nSearch input is usable\r\nClear and Role buttons remain visible and easy to tap\r\nRole popover stays within the viewport",
